    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed and meet or exceed required levels for modelRiskLevel 3. All three QoIs pass pre-established acceptance bounds (difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The Test conditions factor was carried as not-assessed on the basis that the standardised F1717 protocol was considered to leave no assessable degrees of freedom; however, this encoding does not satisfy the ASME V&V 40 requirement for explicit factor disposition at elevated risk levels. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support regulatory submission, with the noted encoding gap flagged for resolution in a subsequent revision.",
